.TH .lastlogin "" "" "System Administration"
.PC "Record of last login"
.B $HOME/.lastlogin
.PP
The command
.B login
records in file
.B $HOME/.lastlogin
the date and time you last logged in.
.B login
displays the information the next time you log in.
.PP
If this file does not exist
.B login
assumes that you are a new user, and by default
executes the file
.BR /etc/default/welcome .
This provides a ``friendly'' environment for users
who are using \*(CO for the first time.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "Administering COHERENT," administe
.Xr "login," login
.Xr "Using COHERENT" using_coh
